sentences: Marianne Evelyn Gabriel Faithfull (born 29 December 1946) is an English singer and actress.
She achieved popularity in the 1960s with the release of her hit single
Born in Hampstead, London, Faithfull began her career in 1964 after attending a Rolling Stones party, where she was discovered by Andrew Loog Oldham.
Her debut album Marianne Faithfull (1965) (released simultaneously with her album Come My Way) was a commercial success followed by a number of albums on Decca Records.
From 1966 to 1970, she had a highly publicised romantic relationship with Mick Jagger.
Her popularity was further enhanced by her film roles, such as those in I'll Never Forget What's'isname (1967), The Girl on a Motorcycle (1968), and Hamlet (1969).
